<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 21 at 1:27PM EDT until July 21 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 PM EDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN ALAMANCE...NORTHWESTERN RANDOLPH AND GUILFORD
COUNTIES...
At 126 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Monroeton to near McLeansville to 6 miles south of
Greensboro to 7 miles southeast of Thomasville, moving east at 30
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, High Point, Randleman, McLeansville, Archdale,
Summerfield, Trinity, Gibsonville, Pleasant Garden and Jamestown.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
